The applicant must have a DDS/DMD/BDS degree, as well as a PhD degree in a field related to anaesthesia or an EdD, at the time of appointment. The candidate must have successfully completed advanced training in Dental Anaesthesia in a program whose accreditation has been accepted by the Royal College of Dental Surgeons of Ontario or the Commission on Dental Accreditation in the United States. Applicants must have at least one year of appropriate clinical experience in Dental Anaesthesia and be eligible for or have obtained a specialist certificate of registration in Ontario in Dental Anaesthesia.

We seek enthusiastic and innovative individuals with a demonstrated record of teaching excellence, as well as a demonstrated ability to enhance the domestic and international reputation of our programs and significantly add to the quality of the student experience. Additionally, candidates must possess a demonstrated commitment to excellent pedagogical practice and a demonstrated interest in teaching-related scholarly activities.

